# Technical Implementation Plan: Nethaji Portfolio

This document outlines the technical approach to building Nethaji's personal portfolio website.

## Objective
To build a modern, responsive, and maintainable single-page developer portfolio using React (Vite) and Tailwind CSS, tailored specifically for "Nethaji".

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> Please review the proposed architecture and tech stack detailed below.
> Is Tailwind CSS acceptable for styling, or would you prefer pure CSS modules? The plan currently assumes Tailwind CSS as it aligns well with modern React development and rapid prototyping.

## Proposed Architecture

1.  **Framework:** React 18+ initialized via Vite.
2.  **Styling:** Tailwind CSS for utility-first, responsive design, and easy dark mode implementation.
3.  **Icons:** `lucide-react` or `react-icons` for clean, modern SVG icons.
4.  **Routing:** Standard scroll-based section navigation on a single page (no external router needed for a simple one-page portfolio).

## Project Structure Changes

### [NEW] Configuration and Core
- `tailwind.config.js`: Configure colors, fonts, and dark mode (`class` strategy).
- [src/index.css](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Documents/React_Project/nethaji-portfolio/src/index.css): Tailwind directives and global custom styles (e.g., smooth scrolling, custom scrollbars).
- [src/App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Documents/React_Project/nethaji-portfolio/src/App.tsx): Main layout container bringing together Navbar, Footer, and all sections.
- [src/main.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Documents/React_Project/nethaji-portfolio/src/main.tsx): Entry point.

### [NEW] Utilities & Hooks
- `src/hooks/useTheme.js`: Custom hook to manage Light/Dark mode state and synchronize it with `localStorage` and the `documentElement` class.
- `src/utils/helpers.js`: Utility functions (e.g., combining class names, formatting dates).

### [NEW] Constants (Data Management)
- `src/constants/personalInfo.js`: Name, title, contact details, social links.
- `src/constants/skills.js`: Structured list of skills (e.g., Frontend, Backend, Tools).
- `src/constants/projects.js`: Array of project objects (title, description, tech stack, links).
- `src/constants/experience.js`: Array of work/education experience objects.

### [NEW] Reusable Components (`src/components/common/`)
- `SectionTitle.jsx`: Standardized heading for each portfolio section.
- `SkillCard.jsx`: Reusable card to display a single skill.
- `ProjectCard.jsx`: Reusable card for project details.
- `SocialLinks.jsx`: Component to render GitHub, LinkedIn, etc.
- `ThemeToggle.jsx`: Sun/Moon button to switch themes.

### [NEW] Layout & Sections (`src/components/`)
- `Navbar.jsx`: Sticky header with navigation links and theme toggle.
- `Hero.jsx`: Intro section with name, title, and quick summary.
- `About.jsx`: Detailed background information.
- `Skills.jsx`: Grid of `SkillCard` components based on `constants/skills.js`.
- `Projects.jsx`: Grid of `ProjectCard` components based on `constants/projects.js`.
- `Experience.jsx`: Timeline or list view of `constants/experience.js`.
- `Contact.jsx`: Contact form or direct contact links.
- `Footer.jsx`: Copyright and bottom social links.

### [NEW] Pages (`src/pages/`)
- `Home.jsx`: Assembles all the individual sections into the main scrollable page.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Build Verification
- Verify successful build using `npm run build` to ensure no TypeScript or bundling errors.
- Run `npm run lint` if ESLint is configured.

### Manual Verification Steps
1.  **Start Development Server:** Run `npm run dev`.
2.  **Visual Inspection (Desktop):** Open the local URL and check the overall layout, typography, and spacing.
3.  **Visual Inspection (Mobile):** Use browser dev tools to simulate a mobile device and ensure all sections stack correctly and the navigation works.
4.  **Theme Functional Test:** Click the Theme Toggle button in the Navbar. Verify the background and text colors invert appropriately. Refresh the page to ensure the preference is saved in `localStorage`.
5.  **Scroll Navigation:** Click navigation links in the Navbar to verify smooth scrolling to the respective sections.
6.  **Data Rendering:** Ensure data from the `constants` files is correctly displayed in the Skills, Projects, and Experience sections without hardcoded fallbacks affecting the UI.
